<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Overflow Scroll Example</title>
	<style>
		.container {
			width: 300px;
			height: 200px;
			overflow: scroll;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<p>To handle overflow using scroll in HTML, you can add the CSS property overflow: scroll;
             to the container element. This will add a scroll bar to the container element whenever its content overflows.
             In this program, we have a container div element with a class of container. 
             We've set its width and height to 300px and 200px respectively, and added the overflow: scroll; 
             CSS property to it. Inside the container, we have a p element with some dummy text that overflows the container's height.
             When you open this program in a web browser, you'll see that the container element has a scroll bar that you can use to scroll through the overflowing content.</p>
	</div>
</body>
</html>